TextBody:
ref:_00D7091pB._500Q000CQ183:ref

Hello Team,

We have escalated the issue to the Netwrix Team, and they have a few questions about the situation. Could you please respond to these questions so that they can better identify the cause of the issue?

Note : "Alerts are copies created for the logs that customer can consult/ audit under "Reports and Analisys" section and that are delivered via email to EPP admin/s selected in the corresponding Alert/s."


  *
Can we confirm if the interval during which email alerts were not received in the EPP admin/s inboxes happened during the weekend/ a Bank Holiday when users were out of office?

  *
 Has the customer noticed logs missing from "Reports and Analisys" section for the exact same interval?

  *
Has this happened after applying the Security Hotfix #1 coming with Security Advisory ADV-2024-002 that that was released on 27th June 2024 or after applying a specific upgrade for the EPP server and/or EPP clients?

Please Find Netwrix Team's Response Below.

"Answers to the above question would help describe the context for the reported case.
We can also make recommendation for the customer to check if there were problems with the email services or the account used inside Endpoint Protector > System Settings > Email Server Settings (that are both services external to EPP) or advise to check if EPP Admins edited the Alerts section before/ within the interval the alerts were not reaching the inbox (Reports and Analisys > Admin Actions > select "Alerts" from the "UI Section:" dropdown > click the Apply button ).

However, since the described case no longer reproduces, we cannot see the incident in action and therefore there is no data to show a malfunctioning feature/ setting.

As the Endpoint Protector appliance is hosted in customer's environment, our team does not have access to it (only via pre-scheduled remote sessions where the customer allows us access to the system) and therefore there is no correlation between the moment it was noticed that alerts are reaching again the inbox and the moment the case was raised with our team, I would say it's just a coincidence.

If indeed there is an issue related to the "Alerts" feature, for sure that will be reproducing in the very near future and that will allow the team to collect the necessary data to start an investigation."

Thanks & Regards
Nayan Rajore

Subject: Re: Netwrix Support Ticket #413394 - - Not receiving email alert for the USB copy [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0CQ183:ref ]

Hello Team,

We have escalated the issue to the Netwrix Team, and they have a few questions about the situation. Could you please respond to these questions so that they can better identify the cause of the issue?

Note : "Alerts are copies created for the logs that customer can consult/ audit under "Reports and Analisys" section and that are delivered via email to EPP admin/s selected in the corresponding Alert/s."


  *   Can we confirm if the interval during which email alerts were not received in the EPP admin/s inboxes happened during the weekend/ a Bank Holiday when users were out of office?


  *    Has the customer noticed logs missing from "Reports and Analisys" section for the exact same interval?


  *   Has this happened after applying the Security Hotfix #1 coming with Security Advisory ADV-2024-002 that that was released on 27th June 2024 or after applying a specific upgrade for the EPP server and/or EPP clients?
Please Find Netwrix Team's Response Below.

"Answers to the above question would help describe the context for the reported case.
We can also make recommendation for the customer to check if there were problems with the email services or the account used inside Endpoint Protector > System Settings > Email Server Settings (that are both services external to EPP) or advise to check if EPP Admins edited the Alerts section before/ within the interval the alerts were not reaching the inbox (Reports and Analisys > Admin Actions > select "Alerts" from the "UI Section:" dropdown > click the Apply button ).

However, since the described case no longer reproduces, we cannot see the incident in action and therefore there is no data to show a malfunctioning feature/ setting.

As the Endpoint Protector appliance is hosted in customer's environment, our team does not have access to it (only via pre-scheduled remote sessions where the customer allows us access to the system) and therefore there is no correlation between the moment it was noticed that alerts are reaching again the inbox and the moment the case was raised with our team, I would say it's just a coincidence.

If indeed there is an issue related to the "Alerts" feature, for sure that will be reproducing in the very near future and that will allow the team to collect the necessary data to start an investigation."

Thanks & Regards
Nayan Rajore
